07/15/2020
Java Recap: Arrays: single & multi-dimensional
            for each loop


package name: day27_recap

ARRAY'S SIZE IS FIXED


single dimensional: a variable that contains elements (Collection of elements)
            each element has index

    declare:
        DataType[]  name = {data1, data2, data3..}
                             0       1      2

     initialize size only:
           DataType[]  name = new  DataType[length]

           default values:
                int, long, byte, short ===> 0
                float, double ===> 0.0
                boolean ==> false
                String ==> null


    Arrays.toString(name): converts array to string


length -1 ==> last index


for each loop: WE MUST HAVE A DATA STRUCTURE IN ORDER TO USE

        iteration order(fixed) : 0 ~ length -1

              for( DataType  name : Collection of data ){
                    statements;
              }

          when to use?
            when we dont need to provide indexes



mult-dimensional array: a variable that contains arrays


        Arrays.deepToString()